50|$|The Kingdom {{underwent}} a crucial change in 1921 {{to the dismay}} of Croatia's largest political <b>party,</b> the <b>Croatian</b> <b>Peasant</b> <b>Party</b> (Hrvatska seljačka stranka). The new constitution abolished the historical/political entities, including Croatia and Slavonia, centralizing authority in the capital of Belgrade. The <b>Croatian</b> <b>Peasant</b> <b>Party</b> boycotted the government of the Serbian People's Radical Party throughout the period, except for a brief interlude between 1925 and 1927, when external Italian expansionism was at hand with her allies, Albania, Hungary, Romania and Bulgaria that threatened Yugoslavia as a whole.|$|R
